  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The main purpose of this study is to assess the efficacy of preoperative embolization in
      decreasing operative blood loss, decreasing the need for intraoperative transfusion and
      facilitate surgical resection in metastatic spine surgery. Furthermore the study aims at
      describing the vascularity in a series of spinal metastasis, and to correlate this with
      perioperative blood loss.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
